# Troubleshooting Scenarios

## Scenario 1 – DNS Misconfiguration

Symptom:
Client unable to join domain.

Root Cause:
Incorrect DNS server configured on client.

Resolution:
Set client DNS to domain controller IP.
Validated via:
nslookup corp.local

---

## Scenario 2 – Primary Domain Controller Failure

Symptom:
DC1 powered off.

Action:
Validated replication health before outage.
Tested authentication and domain join via DC2.

Result:
Authentication remained operational.

---

## Scenario 3 – DHCP Relay Misconfiguration

Symptom:
Client not receiving IP address.

Root Cause:
Incorrect relay target IP on pfSense.

Resolution:
Corrected relay configuration.
Validated lease acquisition from AD DHCP server.
